  "prompt": "Why was the Adidas cotton deodorant discontinued? What did customers think of it?",
  "response": "The Adidas cotton deodorant was discontinued primarily because **Adidas chose to focus on other product lines and fragrances within their deodorant range.** Discontinuations in the personal care industry are often driven by:\n\n*   **Shifting market trends:** Consumer preferences change, and companies adapt by prioritizing products with higher sales potential.\n*   **Profitability:** Certain products may not be as profitable to produce or market as others.\n*   **Streamlining product lines:** Companies often consolidate their offerings to reduce complexity and costs.\n*   **Introduction of newer products:** Replacing older products with newer, more innovative options is a common strategy.\n\n**Customer Opinions:**\n\nCustomer opinions on the Adidas cotton deodorant were generally **positive**. Many liked:\n\n*   **The clean, fresh, and subtle scent:** The \"cotton\" fragrance was often described as light and non-overpowering, making it suitable for everyday use.\n*   **Its effectiveness:** Many users found it to be reliable in controlling odor and providing a feeling of freshness throughout the day.\n*   **The affordability:** Adidas deodorants are generally positioned as budget-friendly options.\n*   **Gentle on sensitive skin:** Some users with sensitive skin found it less irritating than other deodorants.\n\nHowever, some customers also had negative experiences:\n\n*   **Some users didn't find it effective enough for high levels of activity or strong body odor.**\n*   **Scent was too light:** Some found it to be overly mild, even undetectable after a short period.\n*   **White marks:** Some complained of white marks on clothing, a common issue with some antiperspirant/deodorant formulations.\n\nThe discontinuation was disappointing for many loyal users who appreciated its unique scent and effectiveness. They have expressed their disappointment in online forums and sought alternatives with similar fragrance profiles.",
